# BKG Rat Vote Rules

When a blocker is detected, Agent Rat starts automatically:

1. Architect proposes solution
2. Builder evaluates feasibility
3. Reviewer checks quality
4. Product validates business value
5. Contrarian challenges assumptions
6. Growth considers impact

Vote outcomes: approved, rejected, revise, blocked.

Threshold: majority (>50%) of non-abstaining votes.
Blocked requires user approval to proceed.
